  "body": "Because a `&T` type is copyable, it is currently possible to close over them using an `fn@()` (and, eventually, `iface@`).  This is clearly wrong.  We need a new kind---perhaps `heap` or `gc`?---indicating data which is not only copyable but also copyable into a shared closure.  This goes in between copy/send, I think.\n",
